    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine Service, Model Year 1994 - 1998 - CRANKCASE, CRANKSHAFT, CONNECTING
        RODS AND PISTONS - Connecting Rods, Pistons and Piston Rings - Disassembly
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Disassembly</title>
        <figure id="f1200725" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg2/EG2584.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="472px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Removing the Piston Rings</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Piston Ring Expander Tool</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Piston</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Piston Ring</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Connecting Rod</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a piston ring expander tool to remove the piston rings. Remove the top ring first, then
                the intermediate ring, and finally the oil control ring.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1200726" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg3/EG3343.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="532px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Removing the Piston Retaining Ring</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Connecting Rod</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Piston</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Retaining Ring</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Separate the connecting rod from the piston as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Use pliers to remove the two piston pin retaining rings.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove the piston pin from the bore by hand.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Separate the connecting rod from the piston.</para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
